    <item>
      <title>Re: Destructive Force AA</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=monkbalance&amp;message.id=11087#M11087</link>
      <description>Most likely, look at the base1 or base2 coding on lucy (i forget which&#xD;
it is).&amp;nbsp; Speedfocus is -25.&amp;nbsp; I forget what hundred hands is&#xD;
and I'm not going to look - but its probably less.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
To be exact, it removes whatever % that amount is from your base&#xD;
delay.&amp;nbsp; So if you have a 20 delay weapon it would take off 5&#xD;
delay.&amp;nbsp; A 100 delay weapon it would take off 25 delay, etc.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
This reduction is INDEPENDANT of any sort of haste.&amp;nbsp; It's always that set amount, and its always applied AFTER haste.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
So no matter what, you're getting that 25% base delay reduction.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
Thats why it is an extremely powerful disc when you have max haste and bard overhaste.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
Example-&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
My epic is a 41/20 weapon and my offhand is a 34+1/20 weapon.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
With max haste (100%) and bard overhaste (30%) the math would be -&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
20/2.3 = 8.7 delay (no I'm not sure exactly how its rounded or if it is rounded)&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
So I would have a 41/8.7 and a 34+1/8.7 weapon.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
When I use speedfocus that would become-&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
current delay (8.7) - (base delay x 0.25) or 20x.25=5) = 8.7-5 = 3.7 delay&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
My weapons for 30seconds in a bard group are then 41/3.7 and&#xD;
34+1/3.7.&amp;nbsp; I suspect it rounds up, but still, you have to admit&#xD;
that having 4 delay weapons is insanely high dps.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
You can imagine the effects of adding in things like 150accuracy, auspice, 2800+atk, champion, shm 2.0, etc etc.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
